<br>
As we know, ONLY the crystalline watchers/devourers/hunters drop the threads, out of the top level spiders. The velium spiders downstairs also drop them, in addition to bp/robe jewels for the velious armor quests.<br>
<br>
You can fight the entrance spiders with just about any group, if not solo them in absence of a group. They're actually really nice exp as well, if you get a good group with a good puller. Threads seem to drop once every three or four crystalline spider kills. However, the threads drop in groups of 2-4 threads. They're thus reasonably common; if you're the only person in a group who needs them, and you complete every tailoring attempt to make the swatches, you can have 15 swatches in a day or two of hunting, easy. As a side note, I can pull every single spider in the entrance ramps area single at 58.<br>
<br>
Velium spiders, down past the kobolds, also drop the threads, in addition to bp/robe jewels, and 55 velious spells. Really good exp and pretty fun with a balanced 55+ group, though quite dangerous, just because they hit so hard that one mistake or lapse in attention can result in a dead chanter. A level 60 puller can pull the velium hunters/stalkers/etc without agro'ing the velium broodlings. Only the broodlings won't agro, so pull them last. The hunters hit for 200+, and most if not all of the mobs down here backstab. The threads drop perhaps a little more commonly than the entrance spiders, but you probably aren't killing as many of these either, so it balances out. The presence of the bp/robe gems usually makes hunting down here more than worth it if you have the group for it, though.<br>
<br>
Ky <p>Olwe tells you, "WOOOOOO HOOOOOOOO I WANNA GO BEAT OFF THINKING ABOUT VERANT IM SO HAPPY"
